> Hummus and pita chips go together like… well, hummus and pita chips! And while they may be a great pairing, we firmly believe that hummus is destined for bigger and better things. This delicious, layered bowl starts with a base of creamy hummus and chewy bulgur, then it's piled with za'atar-spiced chicken, lemony chopped salad, tangy feta sauce, and a sprinkle of fresh dill. This mix of vibrant, crunchy, creamy, and savory components is sure to satisfy. Beat that, chips!

== Tomato Cucumber Salad ==

Wash and dry produce.

Halve and peel @shallot{1}; thinly slice one half and mince remaining. Fill a #small bowl{} with cold water; add sliced shallot and soak. Dice @Roma Tomato{1}(diced). Trim and dice @Persian Cucumber{1}(diced). Zest and quarter @lemon{1}(quartered). Pick and finely chop fronds from @dill{¼%ounce}(finely chopped).

> This helps mellow the sharp bite of the shallot.

Drain sliced shallot, discarding liquid; place in a #medium bowl{}. Toss with tomato, cucumber, juice from half the lemon, a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp}, and 1 TBSP chopped dill (2 TBSP for 4 servings). Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== Bulgur Wheat ==

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add minced shallot; cook until softened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add @bulgur wheat{½%cup}, @water{1%cup}, @chicken stock concentrate{1}, @harissa powder{½%tsp} (we sent more—use the rest as you like), and @salt{½%tsp} (for 4 servings, use 2 cups water, 1 tsp harissa, and 1 tsp salt). Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until water has absorbed and bulgur is tender, ~{12-15%minutes}.

Turn off heat; keep covered until ready to serve.

== Za'atar-Spiced Chicken ==

Meanwhile, pat @chicken cutlets{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with @za'atar spice{½%tbsp} (1 tsp for 4 servings), salt, and pepper.

> Be sure to measure the Za'atar Spice—we sent more.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.

> Work in batches if necessary.

Transfer chicken to a #cutting board{}. Once cool enough to handle, thinly slice crosswise.

== Feta Sauce ==

While chicken cooks, in a second small bowl, combine @sour cream{2%tbsp}, half the @feta cheese{½%cup}, and lemon zest to taste; mash together with a fork.

> If the feta is cold, massage in package first to soften.

Add water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. (It's OK if the sauce isn't completely smooth.)

== To Serve ==

Drain any excess liquid from bulgur; fluff with a fork. Season with salt and pepper to taste.

Spread @hummus{4%tbsp} on one side of each #serving bowl{}. Serve bulgur next to hummus; top with chicken. Top hummus with salad (draining first). Drizzle everything with feta sauce. Garnish with remaining chopped dill if desired. Serve with remaining lemon wedges on the side.